---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CtaBanner from '../../components/CtaBanner.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="701am — Earned Media for Fashion Brands"
  description="In fashion, the brands that endure are not the loudest — they are the ones with a story editors want to tell. Earned media that earns your brand the editorial credibility paid placements can never buy."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Industries', url: '/industries' },
    { name: 'Fashion Brands' },
  ]}
>

  <!-- ════ HERO ════ -->
  <section class="hero" id="top">
    <div class="hero-grain" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-rays" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-sun" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="hero-overline">
        <span class="hero-overline-rule"></span>
        Industries · For fashion brands
        <span class="hero-overline-rule"></span>
      </p>

      <h1 class="hero-headline">
        The label is bought.<br />The <em>story</em> is earned.
      </h1>

      <p class="hero-deck">
        A fashion brand can buy the placement, the influencer, the ad. It cannot buy the editor's belief — and that belief is what turns a label into a name. <em>Earned media is the difference between a brand people scroll past and one they remember.</em>
      </p>

      <div class="cta-cluster">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="/discovery">
          Book a sunrise call
          <span class="btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
        <a class="btn-link" href="#method">
          See how it works
          <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <p class="cta-fine">Thirty minutes. No deck. No pitch. No charge.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ PRESS STRIP ════ -->
  <section class="press-strip" aria-label="Where the fashion story gets told">
    <div class="press-inner">
      <p class="press-label">
        <span class="press-star">★</span>
        Where the fashion story gets told
        <span class="press-star">★</span>
      </p>
      <div class="press-logos">
        <span class="press-logo press-Vogue Business">italic</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-WWD">condensed</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-Hypebeast">roman</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-The Business of Fashion">italic</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-ELLE">condensed</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 01 — THE FIRST TRUTH ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 01 · The first truth</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">A campaign buys a season.<br /><em>A story builds a name.</em></h2>
      <div class="body">
        <p class="dropcap">
          Every emerging fashion brand says the same things: sustainable, crafted, authentic, for the culture. A buyer for a retailer, an editor, a customer with taste — they have heard every one of those words on a thousand lookbooks, so they look past the campaign for the one thing it cannot manufacture: <em>does anyone whose taste I trust actually care about this brand.</em>
        </p>

        <div class="aphorism">Editors confer the credibility ads cannot</div>

        <p>
          That editorial credibility is not bought — a paid placement reads as paid, and the audience knows it. It is earned when a fashion writer chooses to tell <strong>your</strong> story, when your founder's point of view runs in the title the industry reads, when your brand appears where appearing cannot be purchased.
        </p>

        <p>
          The proof is in your own brand right now. The origin only you can tell. The craft no competitor can copy. The cultural moment you are genuinely part of. Each is a story a fashion editor is hunting for and <em>cannot get from a brand chasing the same trend.</em> Most labels spend it all on the campaign. The brands that last invest in the story, and let the editors carry it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 02 — THE LEDGER ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy ledger-section">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 02 · The ledger</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">What an earned placement <em>does for a desk.</em></h2>

      <div class="ledger-grid">
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">15</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Placements earned</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">In one season</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ledger-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">3</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Fashion titles</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">Vogue Business · WWD · BoF</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ledger-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">1</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Un-ignorable story</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">Found in the brand's origin</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ledger-prose">
        <p>
          The pattern repeats across emerging brands. We spend the first weeks finding the story no competitor can claim — an origin, a craft, a cultural truth the brand actually lives — and the rest placing it where buyers and editors already read. <em>The collection changes. The mechanism does not.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="ledger-coda">★ Illustrative of the pattern. Client specifics confidential. ★</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 03 — THE METHOD ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy" id="method">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <p class="proclamation-hinge">
        The office holds the same two articles, whatever the industry on the masthead —
      </p>

      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 03 · The method</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2 h2-dark">Two things. Done <em>without compromise.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-dark body-center">
        <p>
          We do not run your campaign or manage your influencer seeding. We build the conditions under which an editor already believes in your brand before the lookbook lands. <em>The method fits on a single page, and it does not bend for the season.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <article class="doc">
        <header class="doc-header">
          <div class="doc-stamp">★ Tenets of the office ★</div>
          <h3 class="doc-title">The Two Articles of Earned Authority</h3>
          <p class="doc-sub">Adopted at sunrise. Held for the fashion desk.</p>
        </header>

        <div class="tenet">
          <div class="tenet-mark">Art. i</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="tenet-h">Find the angle inside your story.</h4>
            <p class="tenet-p">
              Buried in your origin and your craft is one true sentence about your brand that no competitor can claim and no editor can refuse. <em>It is almost never the thing on the campaign's hero image.</em> We sit with you until we find it, and then we sharpen it until it cuts.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tenet">
          <div class="tenet-mark">Art. ii</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="tenet-h">Place it where the industry reads.</h4>
            <p class="tenet-p">
              A post on your own feed is still your own feed. We do the unglamorous work — the research, the pitch, the follow-up — until the right writer at <em>Vogue Business</em> or <em>BoF</em> tells the story. Then we do it again, until your name is the one editors bring up first.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="doc-sig">
          <p class="doc-sig-line">— 701am, est. at sunrise</p>
          <div class="doc-sig-title">Office of Earned Media</div>
        </div>
        <div class="doc-wax">7:01</div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 04 — THE WORK ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy" id="work">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 04 · The work</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">Three engagements.<br /><em>Built for the desk.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-center">
        <p>
          Three ways the office goes to work on a fashion brand. <em>Pick the one that fits the season you are in.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="stamp-rule">
        <div class="stamp-rule-bar"></div>
        <div class="stamp-rule-time">7:01</div>
        <div class="stamp-rule-bar"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="eng-grid">
        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">i.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement I · The fastest</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Mine the <em>brand story.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            We turn your origin and your craft into a single editor-ready angle — the story a fashion writer wants to tell, not the campaign you want to run.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Brand &amp; origin audit</li>
            <li>One un-ignorable thesis</li>
            <li>Editor-ready memo</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">ii.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement II · The campaign</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Own the <em>season's narrative.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            A sustained placement campaign across the titles buyers and editors read. Your founder becomes the named voice on the cultural moment your brand is part of.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Pitch · place · follow-up</li>
            <li>Vogue Business · WWD · BoF</li>
            <li>Founder positioning</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">iii.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement III · The engine</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Arm your <em>internal team.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            The earned-media skills your brand or comms lead can run themselves — pitch craft, editor research, the angle-finder — tuned to the fashion beat and built to outlast any one season.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Earned-media playbook</li>
            <li>Fashion press list</li>
            <li>Repeatable, in-house</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ FOUNDER NOTE ════ -->
  <section class="founder-note">
    <div class="founder-inner reveal">
      <p class="founder-eyebrow">
        <span class="founder-rule"></span>
        A note from the office
        <span class="founder-rule"></span>
      </p>
      <blockquote class="founder-quote">
        There are a thousand labels chasing the same trend with a bigger campaign. There are perhaps a handful an editor would choose to write about. <em>We are built to make you one of them.</em> If the credibility you want is the kind ads can't buy, the sunrise call is free.
      </blockquote>
      <p class="founder-sig">
        <span class="founder-name">— David</span>
        <span class="founder-time">at 7:01</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § — FROM THE FIELD ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ — From the field</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">What the desk <em>hears back.</em></h2>

      <div class="field-grid">
        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            They found the thread in our founding story we had never thought to tell. The BoF feature that followed put us on three buyers' radars in a week.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">Founder &amp; Creative Director</span>
            <span class="field-role">Emerging ready-to-wear label</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            We had spent the whole budget on a campaign nobody remembered. One earned story in WWD did what the campaign couldn't — it made editors take us seriously.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">Co-founder</span>
            <span class="field-role">Accessories brand</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            What I paid for was placements. What I got was an editorial point of view the whole brand now runs on. Every collection since is downstream of it.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">Brand Director</span>
            <span class="field-role">Sustainable fashion house</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <p class="ledger-coda">★ Names withheld where confidentiality required. Words unchanged. ★</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ CTA ════ -->
  <CtaBanner
    eyebrow="The work begins at 7:01"
    heading="Ready to be the brand <em>editors choose?</em>"
    body="Thirty minutes. We listen, find the story hiding in your brand's origin, and tell you straight whether we can earn you the editorial credibility a campaign can't buy."
    primaryLabel="Book a sunrise call"
    primaryHref="/discovery"
    secondaryLabel="Or read the field manual"
    secondaryHref="/legend-maker"
  />

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ─────── WHO THIS IS FOR — buyer-segment cards (optional) ─────── */
  .aud-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    background: var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .aud-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5));
    position: relative;
  }
  .aud-card + .aud-card { border-left: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
  .aud-tag {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
  }
  .aud-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "dlig" 1;
    font-size: var(--f4-size);
    line-height: 1.1;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .aud-h em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--claret); }
  .aud-p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
  }
  .aud-p em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); }
  .aud-line {
    margin: 0;
    padding-top: var(--x4);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.10em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ─────── ENGAGEMENTS — mirrors the index "offers" three-up ─────── */
  .eng-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    background: var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .eng-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5));
    position: relative;
  }
  .eng-card + .eng-card { border-left: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
  .eng-num {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: var(--f3-size);
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-variant-numeric: oldstyle-nums;
    margin-bottom: var(--x4);
  }
  .eng-tier {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--x4);
  }
  .eng-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "dlig" 1;
    font-size: var(--f4-size);
    line-height: 1.12;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .eng-h em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--claret); }
  .eng-p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
  }
  .eng-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: var(--x4) 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .eng-list li {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    padding: var(--x5) 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--x4);
    counter-increment: eng;
  }
  .eng-list { counter-reset: eng; }
  .eng-list li::before {
    content: counter(eng, lower-roman) ".";
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-size: 12px;
    min-width: 1.4em;
  }

  /* ─────── FROM THE FIELD — mirrors the index testimonial cards ─────── */
  .field-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--x3);
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
  }
  .field-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--claret);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5)) var(--x2);
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .field-mark {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 3rem;
    line-height: 0.5;
    height: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--claret);
  }
  .field-quote {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
    flex: 1;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .field-by {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding-top: var(--x4);
  }
  .field-name {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--f5-size);
    color: var(--claret);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .field-role {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: var(--x5);
  }

  /* ─────── RESPONSIVE ─────── */
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .aud-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .aud-card + .aud-card { border-left: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
    .eng-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .eng-card + .eng-card { border-left: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
    .field-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
